The Healing Power of Prevention
Prevention is often imagined as protection only — a shield against illness before it begins. Yet in our vision, complete prophylaxis reveals a surprising dimension: its healing capacity.
A balanced diet can overcome minor conditions.
The synergy of preventive methods — medicinal plants, fasting (autophagy), and procedures on the body’s meridians — can confront diseases even in more advanced stages.
When combined, these resources do not merely defend health; they actively restore it.
This association of methods creates a colossal healing force. Prevention, therefore, is not only about avoiding illness — it is about reclaiming vitality, even when disease has already taken root.


